cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of making mobile processes (agents) gather or converge at a same position. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with distributed processes and their coordination. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper presents a new model and analyzes the solvability of the gathering and convergence problems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with the behavior of a system of mobile processes and their convergence. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with physical robots, but the problem of gathering and convergence is relevant to robotics.
